title: For Sale:  Ohio Ordnance Works VZ2000 (Czech VZ58) 7.62×39mm
postcontent: While externally similar to the AK, the VZ58 was the Czech's answer to the AK and boasts a different (better) short stroke gas pistol operating system that's striker fired instead of hammer fired, has a milled steel receiver instead of a flimsy stamped receiver - while still being a good deal lighter. The VZ does use proprietary mags, but they're both lighter and stronger than AK mags. The VZ also has a less cumbersome safety that can be easily manipulated with your trigger finger vs having to sweep your whole hand like with an AK. The simpler safety has the added benefit of not exposing the guts of the gun to the elements while in the safe position. The VZ58 also holds the bolt open after the last round is fired. This would be a great truck or SHTF gun.This rifle (dubbed the VZ2000) was made by Ohio Ordnance Works to incredibly exacting standards (Google some reviews - they're all great) right here in the USA and includes four (4) mags with pig skin bandoleer, a bayonet w/sheath, cleaning kit, sling, folding stock (will come with the fixed stock on it, but it's an easy swap), manual, and I'll throw in 100 rounds of TulAmmo 154gr soft point steel case non-corrosive ammo to get you started.I have two of these rifles. One is unfired. The other has 60 rounds of non-corrosive ammo (see above) through it. Price is for each, not both.Decent video overview on YouTube at https://youtu.be/4rxiOW5bIYEBuyer must be willing to complete purchase at an FFL. Seller will pay for buyer's background check.
